Intialize a character variable in a program and 
if the value is alphabet then print "Alphabet" 
if itâ€™s a number then print "Digit" and 
for other characters print "Special Character"


import java.util.*;
class Alphadigit
{
public static void main(String args[]){
Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
char var=sc.nextLine().charAt(0);
if(var>='a' && var <= 'z'){
System.out.println("it is an alphabet => "+var);
}
else if(Character.isDigit(var)){
System.out.println("it is a digit => "+var);
}
else{
System.out.println("it is a special character");}
}
}
